text: Sekolah Menengah Kebangsaan Taman Desa Tebrau also known with the abbreviation SMKTDT is a secondary school located in Jalan Harmonium 22, Taman Desa Tebrau, Johor, Malaysia. ==History== SMK Taman Desa Tebrau was established on 2 September 2003. The school building has five blocks of three classrooms and an administrative block, a block of laboratories, music rooms and a block for Studio Art and Life Skills and Engineering Technology as well as a prayer room facilities, and cafeteria. Other than that, the school also has a basketball court and a big field for students' Physical Education v Physical Education, it is also known as Pendidikan Jasmani in Malay language. In year 2014, a student named Rosalyn Chan Li Zhen scored 9 A+ in SPM examination, the O level. Other than that, SMK Taman Desa Tebrau had host for the secondary school basketball competition in Pasir Gudang area for 3 consecutive years from 2013. The school was opened on 5 January 2004. ==References== Category:2004 establishments in Malaysia Category:Educational institutions established in 2004 Category:Johor Bahru Category:Secondary schools in Malaysia Category:Schools in Johor
